@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit How the UI Finds Out It Is Done

' The worker never tells the UI it finished. It just writes a
' row. Debezium notices the DB change and emits a second event that ends up
' back at the browser. Change Data Capture delivers the completion.

queue "job.requests" as reqs
participant "python-worker" as worker
database "Postgres\npublic.jobs" as pg
participant "Debezium\n(Kafka Connect)" as dbz
queue "orbit.public.jobs\n(CDC topic)" as cdc
participant "node-gateway" as gw
actor "Browser" as browser

reqs -> worker : consume { jobId, payload, owner }
worker -> worker : ~3s work\nreverse(payload)
worker -> pg : UPDATE existing row\nstatus = 'completed' (keeps owner)
note right of worker : It flips the queued row to completed and notifies no one.

pg -> dbz : WAL change\n(publication orbit_publication, pgoutput)
dbz -> cdc : produce CDC envelope\n{ after: {...} }
cdc -> gw : consume CDC event
gw -> browser : WebSocket "job-update"\nfor subscribed jobId

note over dbz, cdc : CDC turns a DB write into an event automatically.

@enduml
